A Rt kit or Real time kit is a kit used by kernels to identifiy what order every process has to run
#example:
*There are 2 processes*:
"Steam.exe"
"explorer.exe"
so a rt kit basically lets the kernel put 1 important process at the top of less important processes.
here it'd be:
 -> Steam.exe <---|
 | explorer.exe|'
(here explorer.exe is the importaent one.)
  So yea lets make a rt kit in C(c ,not c# or C++)
                                 
